			"The first line, divided, shows the host going forth according to the rules for such a movement.  If these not be good there will be evil.<br/>\n<br/>\nThe host goes forth according to the rules for such a movement:  if those rules be not observed, there will be evil.\n",
			"The first line, undivided, shows its subject advancing in company with the subject of the second line.  Through his firm correctness there will be good fortune.<br/>\n<br/>\nThe good fortune through the firm correctness of the subject of the first line advancing in company with the subject of the second is due to his will being set on doing what is right.\n",
			"The first line, divided, shows us the superior man who adds humility to humility.  Even the great stream may be crossed with this, and there will be good fortune.<br/>\n<br/>\nThe superior man who adds humility to humility is one who nourishes his virtue in lowliness.\n",
