			"The fourth line, divided, shows the symbol of a sack tied up.  There will be no ground for blame or praise.<br/>\n<br/>\nA sack tied up;  there will be no error:  this shows how, through carefulness, no injury will be received.\n",
			"The fourth line, divided, shows its subject moving right in the center among those represented by the other divided lines, and yet returning alone to his proper path.<br/>\n<br/>\nHe moves right in the center among those represented by the other divided lines, and yet returns alone:  his object is to pursue the proper path.\n",
			"The fourth line, divided, shows the host in retreat.  There is no error.<br/>\n<br/>\nThe host is in retreat; but there is no error:  there has been no failure in the regular course.\n",
