			"In the fifth line, undivided,  we see him who brings the distress and obstruction to a close; the great man and fortunate.  But let him 'say, we may perish, we may perish!', so shall the state of things become firm, as if bound to a clump of bushy mulberry trees.<br/>\n<br/>\nThe good fortune of the great man arises from the correctness of his position.\n",
